    bf:summary [ a bf:Summary ;
            rdfs:label "\"In 1955 more than 150 flag designs were submitted to the Council of Europe in Strasbourg. In December of that year, the Council announced its decision to use twelve yellow stars on a blue background. Each of the rejected designs reflects a distinct vision of Europe. In this book, they are all being published for the first time\"--Page 4 of cover"@en ] ;
